ave Games\", \"from\": 614, \"to\": 630}, {\"ngram\": \"the course\", \"from\": 649, \"to\": 659}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic spirit\", \"from\": 727, \"to\": 745}, {\"ngram\": \"the streets\", \"from\": 754, \"to\": 765}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After the soulless concrete bowls of an ill-conceived Olympic Park on the outskirts of Rio, and the Covid-enforced anonymity of Tokyo, Paris levered its iconic landmarks into front and centre of a Games to which the fans flocked by tram, by Metro and by electric bike.\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 1036, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 855, \"end\": 858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999902613646007, \"rank\": 9.738730192169691e-06, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 896, \"end\": 901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999803271751, \"rank\": 1.9668471736111977e-08, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 903, \"end\": 908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.42683134105786e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the soulless concrete bowls\", \"from\": 774, \"to\": 801}, {\"ngram\": \"an ill-conceived Olympic Park\", \"from\": 805, \"to\": 834}, {\"ngram\": \"the outskirts\", \"from\": 838, \"to\": 851}, {\"ngram\": \"the Covid-enforced anonymity\", \"from\": 864, \"to\": 892}, {\"ngram\": \"its iconic landmarks\", \"from\": 917, \"to\": 937}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 943, \"to\": 948}, {\"ngram\": \"centre\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 959}, {\"ngram\": \"a Games\", \"from\": 963, \"to\": 970}, {\"ngram\": \"the fans\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 988}, {\"ngram\": \"tram\", \"from\": 1000, \"to\": 1004}, {\"ngram\": \"Metro\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1014}, {\"ngram\": \"electric bike\", \"from\": 1022, \"to\": 1035}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If Paris underscored one particular legacy for the at times turbulent 12-year reign of outgoing International Olympic Committee president Thomas Bach, it may well have been his overseeing of the expansion of the urban programme that once again provided some of the Games' most indelible memories.\", \"from\": 1038, \"to\": 1334, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1041, \"end\": 1046, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.42683134105786e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1134, \"end\": 1165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1176, \"end\": 1187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one particular legacy\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1080}, {\"ngram\": \"the at times\", \"from\": 1085, \"to\": 1097}, {\"ngram\": \"turbulent 12-year reign\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1121}, {\"ngram\": \"his overseeing\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1225}, {\"ngram\": \"the expansion\", \"from\": 1229, \"to\": 1242}, {\"ngram\": \"the urban programme\", \"from\": 1246, \"to\": 1265}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games' most indelible memories\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1333}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris, long Europe's epicentre of hip-hop culture, proved the perfect city to showcase that shift in focus, at a time when precarious geo-politics and especially the ongoing rancour with Russia make the relevance of the Games far from certain, and the accent on youth more important than ever.\", \"from\": 1336, \"to\": 1629, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1336, \"end\": 1341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.42683134105786e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1523, \"end\": 1529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999991286889939, \"rank\": 7.458206957066667e-07, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"long Europe's epicentre\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1366}, {\"ngram\": \"hip-hop culture\", \"from\": 1370, \"to\": 1385}, {\"ngram\": \"the perfect city\", \"from\": 1394, \"to\": 1410}, {\"ngram\": \"that shift\", \"from\": 1423, \"to\": 1433}, {\"ngram\": \"focus\", \"from\": 1437, \"to\": 1442}, {\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1453}, {\"ngram\": \"precarious geo-politics\", \"from\": 1459, \"to\": 1482}, {\"ngram\": \"especially the ongoing rancour\", \"from\": 1487, \"to\": 1517}, {\"ngram\": \"the relevance\", \"from\": 1535, \"to\": 1548}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1561}, {\"ngram\": \"the accent\", \"from\": 1584, \"to\": 1594}, {\"ngram\": \"youth\", \"from\": 1598, \"to\": 1603}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Watched by an admiring Bach at stage-side, 25-year-old B-girl Ami top-rocked and froze her way to the Olympics' first breakdancing gold, while Australia's Arisa Trew won a ska