\"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 3168, \"end\": 3195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Olympic Association\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 3200, \"end\": 3208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK Sport\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A plunge\", \"from\": 3034, \"to\": 3042}, {\"ngram\": \"the official medal table\", \"from\": 3048, \"to\": 3072}, {\"ngram\": \"the confines\", \"from\": 3148, \"to\": 3160}, {\"ngram\": \"funding\", \"from\": 3237, \"to\": 3244}, {\"ngram\": \"the cycle\", \"from\": 3249, \"to\": 3258}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But those who broke through back home did not necessarily need to step atop the Olympic podium.\", \"from\": 3289, \"to\": 3384, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic podium\", \"from\": 3365, \"to\": 3383}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For every glorious Bryony-bounce and lung-bursting Keely Hodgkinson charge there were heroic near-misses and heart-warming stories offered by the likes of weightlifter Emily Campbell and shooting mum Amber Rutter.\", \"from\": 3385, \"to\": 3598, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3436, \"end\": 3452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}, {\"begin\": 3553, \"end\": 3567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Campbell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emily Campbell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Campbell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Campbell\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"heroic near-misses\", \"from\": 3471, \"to\": 3489}, {\"ngram\": \"heart-warming stories\", \"from\": 3494, \"to\": 3515}, {\"ngram\": \"the likes\", \"from\": 3527, \"to\": 3536}, {\"ngram\": \"mum\", \"from\": 3581, \"to\": 3584}, {\"ngram\": \"Amber Rutter\", \"from\": 3585, \"to\": 3597}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A dark and at times melancholy ceremony drifted through a story of a Golden Voyager, who purported to take the take the watching world on a dreamlike quest to the very foundations of humanity, but the thousands of athletes ringing the Stade de France were itching for a party.\", \"from\": 3600, \"to\": 3876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3835, \"end\": 3850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A dark\", \"from\": 3600, \"to\": 3606}, {\"ngram\": \"times\", \"from\": 3614, \"to\": 3619}, {\"ngram\": \"melancholy ceremony\", \"from\": 3620, \"to\": 3639}, {\"ngram\": \"a story\", \"from\": 3656, \"to\": 3663}, {\"ngram\": \"a Golden Voyager\", \"from\": 3667, \"to\": 3683}, {\"ngram\": \"the take\", \"from\": 3707, \"to\": 3715}, {\"ngram\": \"the watching world\", \"from\": 3716, \"to\": 3734}, {\"ngram\": \"a dreamlike quest\", \"from\": 3738, \"to\": 3755}, {\"ngram\": \"the very foundations\", \"from\": 3759, \"to\": 3779}, {\"ngram\": \"humanity\", \"from\": 3783, \"to\": 3791}, {\"ngram\": \"the thousands\", \"from\": 3797, \"to\": 3810}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 3814, \"to\": 3822}, {\"ngram\": \"a party\", \"from\": 3868, \"to\": 3875}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was duly provided by Tom Cruise, who skydived in from the top of the cavernous arena, and finally, belatedly, bizarrely, by Snoop himself, who having popped up everywhere in Paris for the best part of two weeks, re-appeared on the big screen safely ensconced back in the sun-kissed climes of California.\", \"from\": 3878, \"to\": 4184, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3902, \"end\": 3912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}, {\"begin\": 4055, \"end\": 4060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.42683134105786e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4173, \"end\": 4183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 0.9999999999895408, \"rank\": 1.0476230659127758e-11, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the top\", \"from\": 3935, \"to\": 3942}, {\"ngram\": \"the cavernous arena\", \"from\": 3946, \"to\": 3965}, {\"ngram\": \"Snoop\", \"from\": 4005, \"to\": 4010}, {\"ngram\": \"the best part\", \"from\": 4065, \"to\": 4078}, {\"ngram\": \"two weeks\", \"from\": 4082, \"to\": 4091}, {\"ngram\": \"the big screen\", \"from\": 4108, \"to\": 4122}, {\"ngram\": \"the sun-kissed climes\", \"from\": 4148, \"to\": 4169}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The vast stage in the centre of the Stade de France remained empty, the athletes drifted slowly away.\", \"from\": 4186, \"to\": 4287, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The vast stage\", \"from\": 4186, \"to\": 4200}, {\"ngram\": \"the centre\", \"from\": 4204, \"to\": 4214}, {\"ngram\": \"the Stade de France\", \"from\": 4218, \"to\": 4237}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 4254, \"to\": 4266}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tomorrow, the chain-link fencing will be pulled down and its famous monuments will once again stand in glorious isolation.\", \"from\": 4288, \"to\": 4410, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the chain-link fencing\", \"from\": 4298, \"to\": 4320}, {\"ngram\": \"its famous monuments\", \"from\": 4345, \"to\": 4365}, {\"ngram\": \"glorious isolation\", \"from\": 4391, \"to\": 4409}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite a somewhat shipwrecked start, and more than a few discordant notes, Paris has given LA some act to follow in bringing the Olympic Games back to the people.\", \"from\": 4412, \"to\": 4575, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4488, \"end\": 4493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.42683134105786e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a somewhat shipwrecked start\", \"from\": 4420, \"to\": 4448}, {\"ngram\": \"more than a few discordant notes\", \"from\": 4454, \"to\": 4486}, {\"ngram\": \"LA\", \"from\": 4504, \"to\": 4506}, {\"ngram\": \"some act\", \"from\": 4507, \"to\": 4515}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 4538, \"to\": 4555}, {\"ngram\": \"the people\", \"from\": 4564, \"to\": 4574}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Impartial news + intelligent debate All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 4577, \"to\": 4634, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Impartial news + intelligent debate\", \"from\": 4577, \"to\": 4612}, {\"ngram\": \"All rights\", \"from\": 4613, \"to\": 4623}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 2026 Associated Newspapers Limited.\", \"from\": 4635, \"to\": 4